\text{Given}\;\;\frac{2}{x\ln(4)}, \;\;\text{how does it reduce to}\; \frac{1}{x\ln(2)}\quad ?
\ln\left(a^b\right) = b \ln(a)
\frac{2}{x\ln(4)} = \frac{2}{x\ln\left(2^2\right)} =  \frac 2{2x\ln (2)} = \frac 1{x\ln (2)}
\log (2^2)=2\log(2)
ln(4)=ln(2^2)=2ln(2)
 \ln(AB)=\ln(A)+\ln(B) 
 \frac{2}{x\ln(4)}=\frac{2}{x(\ln(2)+\ln(2))}=\frac{2}{2x\ln(2)}=\frac{1}{x\ln(2)}. 
